  "narrative_arc": "Arrested for a crime that is never named by a court that never explains itself. Kafka documents the architecture of a legal system that exists to process people, not to deliver justice. K. navigates an infinite bureaucracy — every door opens onto another waiting room, every official defers to another official, the process is the punishment.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "K.'s dome is Layer 1 (Legal) and Layer 2 (Systems) consuming all other layers. His dome maps what happens when bureaucracy becomes the primary condition of existence — when navigating the system IS the full-time job.",
